data.name: gb2.ToolTip
data.value: Step 1: Select the drives you want look in for the given file.If you are interested in Searching only in a particular directory then click the button named 'Browse' Step 2: If you are not at all interested in searching particular directories you can exclude them by clicking the button named 'Exclude Some Directories' and Searching 2006 will not search for given file in these directories Step 3: These results are sufficient to start the Searching process .But you can even specific about your search by Going to Section 3

data.name: rbdate.ToolTip
data.value: Step 1: The option here are to make search for files based on date 1.Modified Date 2.Created Date 3.Accessed Date Choose what is appropriate for you Step 2: Now Select a date from below two fields.From field provides date indicating the old date and To field provides date indicating the new date Once you have completed selecting these.Search 2006 will get files whose date lie between from and to date provided by you Step 3: Now Go to Section 2

data.name: rbword.ToolTip
data.value: Step 1: This is for getting files which contain the given word (not in the file name). So enter a Word to look inside the files or click the drop down list to get words that you have previously searched. Step 2: Go to Section 2 if you have successfully entered the word.

data.name: rbname.ToolTip
data.value: Step 1: Enter a valid file name and the name should not contain characters like \ / : < > You can even give it a regular expression.You can select the drop down list to get the names that you previously searched Step 2: Go to the Section 2 below after entering the requried file name.

data.name: rbsize.ToolTip
data.value: Step 1: This section Will allow you to Search for files based on Size.You can select any of the four options provided 1.Bytes 2.KB 3.MB 4.GB Step 2: Now Give the minimum and maximum sizes.This makes the Search 2006 to get files whose size lies between max size and min size Step 3: Go to Section 2 for selecting drives

data.name: cbsubdir.ToolTip
data.value: Sub Directories ------------------ As the Name indicates if checked Search 2006 will include all the sub directories inside a given drive or given directory. This option is by default Checked

data.name: cbsystemfolder.ToolTip
data.value: System Folders ------------------ This enables Search 2006 to search inside a System folder for example directories like the following c:\WINDOWS\system32\Microsoft c:\WINDOWS\system32\appmgmt\MACHINE e.t.c . This is option is by default enabled.

data.name: cbcase.ToolTip
data.value: Case Sensitive ------------------ This makes Search 2006 to get only files that exactly matches with the given file name if your search criteria is by Name or it get files which contains the word that exactly matches the given word if your search criteria is by Word Note: Remember if this option is checked the word or file name 'Search' is different from 'sEaRch'. That is what Search 2006 Mean
